title: Bacterial Cell Diagram
description: An illustration of a bacterial cell, showing its structure. The cell has a rounded shape with a thick outer membrane and hair-like structures (flagella) protruding from its surface. Inside, there are various components, including a twisted strand representing DNA, and a blue cytoplasm.

title: Electron Microscope
description: An electron microscope is displayed in a laboratory setting. The microscope features a cylindrical body with multiple arms extending from it, and it is connected to a computer monitor. The overall color scheme is predominantly white and gray, with some metallic components.

title: Colorful Frog on Leaf
description: A close-up image of a vibrant frog with a striking pattern of black, orange, and blue colors, perched on a green leaf. The frog's skin showcases intricate details and bright hues, highlighting its unique appearance in a natural setting.

title: Yeast Cells Under Microscope
description: A colorful scanning electron microscope image showing a cluster of yeast cells. The cells are oval-shaped and vary in size, displaying a range of colors that highlight their structure.

title: Microscopic View of Bacteria
description: A close-up, microscopic image showing numerous rod-shaped bacteria. The bacteria are depicted in a green hue, highlighting their elongated forms and clustered arrangement.

title: Mushroom in Greenery
description: A single mushroom with a dark reddish-brown cap and a light brown stem, surrounded by lush green moss and ferns.
